HEADWORD: Undergird
<hw>Un`der*gird"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bind below;
to gird round the bottom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They used helps, <qex>undergirding</qex> the ship.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts xxvii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underglaze</ent>⟦br⟧
